==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brose
<hw>Brose</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF. Gael.
<ets>brothas</ets>. Cf. <er>Brewis</er>, <er>Broth</er>.]</ety>
<def>Pottage made by pouring some boiling liquid on meal (esp. oatmeal),
and stirring it. It is called beef <xex>brose</xex>, water
<xex>brose</xex>, etc., according to the name of the liquid (beef broth,
hot water, etc.) used.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brotel</ent>⟦br⟧
